sql:
SELECT properties.property_id, properties.description, property_types.type_name
FROM properties
INNER JOIN property_types ON properties.type_id = property_types.type_id;

external_knowledge:
- "tenants" refers to the clients who have leased properties;
- "places they are renting" refers to the properties and their descriptions;
- "price tag" refers to the rental rate of the properties.

- "dazzling stars" are metaphorically referring to the properties that are both available and have a rental rate above average; 
- "glowing in the night sky of the real estate market" represents the properties in the market;
- "shining brightly" refers to their above average rental rates;
- "unique identifiers" corresponds to the property_id;
- "types" corresponds to the type_name;
- "rental rates" corresponds to the rental_rate;
- "standing tall above the average" indicates that the rental rate is higher than the average rental rate of all properties;
- "eagerly awaiting their next journey with an open status" implies that the property status is 'available';
- "brilliance" is metaphorically indicating the rental rate.

sql:
SELECT p.property_id, p.description, pf.feature_name
FROM properties p
LEFT JOIN property_features pf ON p.property_id = pf.property_id;
